article.headline: TCU 85, Colorado State 72
article.story: FORT WORTH, Texas (AP) -- Nile Murry scored 24 points as TCU ended a six-game losing streak, beating Colorado State 85-72 on Saturday night. Brent Hackett had 15 and Chudi Chinweze 14 for TCU (5-14, 1-4 Mountain West), which won its first conference game since joining the Mountain West this season. The victory was just the second for the Horned Frogs in their last 10 games. Jason Smith led Colorado State (5-14, 1-4) with 16 points. Michael Harrison scored 14 points and Stephan Gilling had 11 off the bench. The Rams have lost four of their last five. Murry, who scored 21 of his points in the first half, was 11-of-12 from the foul line.
